The Committee, in conjunction with the County Manager's office, shall advise the Board of County Commissioners and shall make recommendations with respect to establishment and implementation of Miami-Dade County's overall plans for the care of victims of trauma. The Committee's recommendations shall be in the areas of:


Coordination with all public and private entities and organizations which are concerned with provision of trauma care;



Formulation of legislative, programmatic and funding agendas needed to address present and future trauma care needs of the community;



Establishment of suggested administrative and medical policies and protocols to enhance the efficiency and quality of trauma care;



Overseeing the development of the State mandated trauma medical services plan;



Performance of any other advisory function assigned to the Committee by the Board.
